{
  "doc_id": "16314",
  "text": "A functional dependency X→A is partial if some attribute B∈X can be removed from X and the dependency still holds. Let A, B, and C be attributes of a relation R, A→B and B→C be two dependencies that hold in R. Then C is transitively dependent on A via B (provided that A is not functionally dependent on B or C) [CITATION_1] .",
